CHOLERA - MEXICO (ACAPULCO)
***************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Wednesday, 15 October 1997
From: Angie Lee (Finchley) <Finchely@aol.com>
Source: OPPT NEWSBREAK and media sources

Cholera has broken out in Acapulco, which was ravaged by a hurricane last
week. Health officials are working to protect residents from the disease,
but a lack of potable water has compounded the risk of the disease, and
there is a serious risk of typhoid, dengue fever, and salmonella.
--
Angie Lee (Finchely)
Special Correspondent
